==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retepore
<hw>Re`te*pore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rete</ets>
a net + <ets>porus</ets> pore.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
several species of bryozoans of the genus <gen>Retepora</gen>. They form
delicate calcareous corals, usually composed of thin fenestrated
fronds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

